@startuml interaktion-ausloesen
title F2 – Interaktions-Auslösung (systemübergreifender Fluss)

actor Spieler
participant "Input System\n(Map: Player)" as Input
participant "FirstPersonController\n(Runtime)" as FPC
participant "PlayerInteractionController\n(Runtime)" as PIC
participant "PhysicsInteractionProbe\n(Runtime, IInteractionProbe + Resolver)" as Probe
participant "InteractionSelector\n(Core, pure Decide)" as Selector
participant "InteractionPromptPresenter\n(Runtime, editor-authored UI)" as Prompt
participant "IInteractable\n(Weltobjekt)" as Target

== Pro Frame: Fokus ermitteln ==
Spieler -> Input : Move / Look
Input -> FPC : Move/Look-Werte
FPC -> FPC : MovementCalculator / LookMath (Core)\nApply: CharacterController + Kamera

PIC -> Probe : QueryCandidates()
Probe --> PIC : Kandidaten (nur IInteractable)
PIC -> Selector : Decide(kandidaten, settings)
Selector --> PIC : InteractionSelection (TargetId | None)

alt HasTarget
  PIC -> Probe : TryResolve(TargetId)
  Probe --> PIC : IInteractable
  PIC -> Prompt : Show(PromptText)
else kein Ziel
  PIC -> Prompt : Hide()
end

== Auslösen ==
Spieler -> Input : Interact
Input -> PIC : interactPressed
PIC -> PIC : InteractionTrigger.ShouldInteract(HasFocus, pressed) (Core)
alt ShouldInteract == true
  PIC -> Target : Interact()
else
  note right of PIC : keine Auslösung
end

note over Selector
  Auswahlregel unverändert aus F1.
  Core kennt weder UnityEngine noch IInteractable.
end note
@enduml
